==English==

===Etymology===
Greek ''[[khaos]]'' 'vast chasm, void'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/keɪɒs/

=== Noun ===
'''chaos''' (''[[uncountable]]'')

====Hyphenation====
'''cha·os'''

#A [[state]] of [[disorder]].
#A [[force]] that seeks to spread disorder.
#(''mathematics'') The [[mathematical]] [[uncertainty]] caused by [[undiscovered]], or [[unperceived]] factors as well as [[natural]] [[variability]] and [[random]] changes.

